				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table  class="bodyline" width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr>	  <td class="helpline"><span class="genmed"><b>Zantir wrote:</b><script type="text/javascript" src="./templates/select_expand_bbcodes.js"></script><script type="text/javascript"><!--	var id = 'SXBB' + (1000 + Math.floor(Math.random() * 5000));	SXBB[id] = new _SXBB(id);	SXBB[id].T['expand'] = 'Expand';	SXBB[id].T['contract'] = 'Contract';	SXBB[id].writeCmd();//--></script>		</span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote"><script type="text/javascript"><!--	SXBB[id].writeDiv();//--></script>I would also welcome something along the lines of a large mana dump that is on a timer.  If a necro could transfer x amount of mana every 5 or 10minutes to a comrade instead of having to use many many 150 mana twitches.
<br />

<br />
For example, it would be much nicer to coordinate large scale single shot mana dumps than the current method where we dump small amounts repeatedly into massive 13-15k mana pools.  I do believe 5 or 10minute recasts on such an ability would maintain balance, just sort of make things less tedious.
<br />

<br />
I also believe lifeburn should have some sort of mod on it that would make it more worthwhile.  Something like a 2-3, maybe even a 2.5xhp would be meaningful perhaps.  I'd say as a long time raider (end game, but not die hard endgame) that would put my burns in the range of  35000-40000, and that would be pretty neat for a 2hr reset.
<br />

<br />
Lastly, I also agree with above talks about letting lich stick across zones and possibly be enhanced to scale with our tss mana costs.
<br />

<br />
Good job with the ideas guys.<script type="text/javascript"><!--	document.write('</div>');//--></script>		</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
A large mana dump is kind of one of those &quot;dual-edged swords&quot; type deals IMO..and this is what I mean.
<br />

<br />
On one hand, it's practical and beneficial for us.  It'd cut down on time it'd take to twitch a rezzed cleric or whatever, it'd help us &quot;stack&quot; well on raids, and make us more valuable in groups..
<br />

<br />
On the other(and this is the bad edge), it reinforces an aspect of our class that really doesn't need to be(twitching) and might become relied upon.  Which would make some clerics say..If your aa is down, just pump me.  As cute as those little dark elf cleric girls are, no thanks.
<br />

<br />
If there's support for it(or anything else..) I'll forward it along, personally I'm hesitant for anything along a mana xfer line.  
<br />

<br />
The lifeburn proposal has already been put in, and I'll talk to him about that at length, I'm sure.
<br />

<br />
Bloodmagic, that fix should go live with tbs launch.
                <br />_________________<br />Jebasiz
<br />
<a href="http://www.cestusdei.org/news.php" target="_blank" class="postlink">Cestus Dei</a>
<br />
Necromancer Class Correspondent
